    public interface BiIterable<T,U>
extends java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<T,U>>
    A "convenience" interface for Iterable<Map.Entry<T, U>>. Introduced for several reasons:
  • It is used extensively by Tree and its implementations. Besides, the class Iterables has several methods designed specifically for BiIterable<T,U>.
  • Typing BiIterable<T,U> requires less efforts than Iterable<Map.Entry<T,U>> and is more expressive.
